cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.DB

The paper deals with discovering events in real time from microblog streams, which involves analyzing highly dynamic graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Scientific Data Management (cs.SD), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Databases (cs.DB). Among these, cs.SI and cs.IR are the most likely categories as they deal directly with analyzing social networks and information retrieval, respectively. cs.SD and cs.DS are also relevant as they deal with managing and analyzing large datasets, while cs.DB deals with database management, which is relevant for storing and retrieving microblog data.
